node.text: Throwback Thursday. A year ago today, I was working on a pilot about the Brides of Dracula with my fave partner-in-crime @maggiekiley.director. Starring the Queen of All Things @iamginatorres as Cleopatra. And @goran_visnjic as the suavest of Counts. And @erinrrichards as the saucy Madame de Sade. And @k8r3is as sweet, innocent Lily. Like so many other projects, we were shut down by the virus. A year later, the ladies haven’t seen the light of day…yet. But here’s a taste of the delicious, vampy fun we were working on…🔥👰🏽👰🏻👰🏼🧛🏻‍♂️🩸🖤💰🎭⭐️👀💥 📺

node.text: We truly saved the best...and scariest...for last. So much love for this cast, crew, writers, and fandom. Part Four finds our witches and mortals facing off against the Eldritch Terrors. And, friends, there will be monsters, sacrifices, last kisses, a satanic battle-of-the-bands, and some very, very special guest stars...before the most epic ending EVER. You are cordially invited to the End of All Things on December 31st, 2020. 🔮🖤🎢🌪⌛️🔥

node.text: If you haven’t watched #KatyKeene, #Riverdale’s sister-show, all episodes are available for streaming on #HBO Max starting midnight tonight!! There is so much HEART in this show--and lots of hearts, too! It’s a romantic-musical-comedy-drama-fairytale-dream set and filmed in the real NYC!! Love these actors, led by @lucyhale and @iamamurray, love this crew, and love these writers and editors. Settle into a warm bubble bath--or blow a few bubbles with your hand soap--and start binging!!! ❤️💋💃🏻👠🧨🍒👗📺👨🏻‍💻🏆

Also THRILLED to be working with genius director/horror auteur @lieselottesoper again! Millwood, here we come! #plloriginalsin 🔥💋🎁🧨🔪🌪☠️

node.text: Happy to be hosting and spending some quality time with my munchkin nieces and nephew for July 4th this week! Here are Gaby and Joaquin, checking in with Spidey at @gapplecomics during their uncle’s weekly visit to the comic book store!!! (They don’t know it, but they’re going to @disneyland on Friday!! Me, too, apparently. Any and all recommendations welcome…) 🏆💪🏼🥴❤️🚑🧨🎥🎁

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa on June 29, 2021 tagging @fish, @thecwriverdale, and @camimendes. May be an image of 5 people, people standing and text.

node.text: Spent the day binge-watching the second half of #Riverdale Season Five with the writers as we start work on Season Six. Afterwards, we raised champagne glasses to toast @camimendes, who plays our raven-haired femme fatale Veronica Lodge. I will *never* forget Cami’s first scene when we shot the pilot. In a matter of two minutes, she *became* Veronica and somehow made an iconic character…even *more* iconic. Happy birthday, Cami!! We know you’re busy making a movie, but we hope you get a chance to celebrate!!! We love you and thank you for being our #endgame. ❤️🏆🎁💋🎉

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa in Vancouver, British Columbia with @thecw, @warnerbrostv, @ledosshaus, @fish, @thecwriverdale, and @riverdaleafter. May be an image of 7 people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'JOSIE SUPER'.

node.text: Aaaand that’s a wrap on Season Five of #Riverdale. So grateful to everyone who worked on this crazy show this crazy year, under crazier-than-usual circumstances. All the writers and directors and editors. And especially our tireless, amazing all-star cast and our beyond heroic crew, who somehow kept the ship on course. (Special shout-out to @robingivens for bringing us home.) Really excited about our next batch of episodes. They’re some of the best we’ve done. And after that, a break. And after that…💥🚀💋🔥💃🏾👯‍♀️🌪🤡👽👀👫👨🏼‍🤝‍👨🏽👠🕷🐍🦂🦋🐀🍒🍔❤️‍🩹💍🤰🏼🌊🎰

node.text: #Riverdale isn’t coming back until August, but that doesn’t mean we’re not burning the midnight oil tonight. Incredibly proud of and grateful to this group of super-star actors, who have been working so hard and for so long under less than ideal circumstances (to put it mildly). Ditto the best damn crew in Vancouver. Pushing in Season Five as though it were Season One. Champions across the board. We’re nearing the finish-line (for now), with an incredible batch of episodes. Well worth the wait. 💪🏼🏆🎢🍿💋💔🎥💰🤭☠️

Photo by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa in ArcLight Cinemas with @arclightcinemas.

node.text: Like so many others, incredibly bummed to hear that the Arclight is closing. My favorite place to see movies. So many fun nights with so many friends. Incredibly smart, friendly, and truly movie-loving staff. I wrote the remake of “Carrie,” it was a torturous experience, but its premiere at the Arclight was magical. @stiffybnyc mom even made me an Arclight pillow. Which I will be hugging even more tightly tonight. RIP Caramel Popcorn 🎥🍿😢💔🤭
